+# 🛒 Product Review Sentiment Analyzer — A 6-Day Learning Journey
+
+Welcome! This isn't just a project repository — it's a **6-day guided learning journey**.
+
+By the end of Day 6, you will have built a real-world AI tool that takes product reviews and tells you:
+- Whether each review is **Positive / Negative / Neutral**
+- A **confidence score** from a Hugging Face model
+- A **reasoning explanation** from an OpenAI LLM
+- **Aspects** being praised or criticized (e.g. *"Delivery: Negative"*)
+- An **overall product score** + most common positive/negative keywords
+- Everything wrapped in a clean **Gradio web interface**
+
+…and all of it logged for tracking, with versioned prompts — the LLMOps way.
+
+---
+
+## 🎯 The Real-World Problem
+
+Businesses receive **thousands of reviews** every day on Amazon, Flipkart, Google Maps, app stores, and more. No human can read them all. They need an AI tool that can:
+
+1. Quickly classify the **mood** of each review
+2. Explain **why** a review is negative or positive
+3. Surface **what customers actually care about** (price, delivery, quality, support…)
+4. Give a **single number** that summarises overall customer happiness
+
+This project solves exactly that.
+
+---
+
+## 🧰 What You'll Use
+
+| Tool | Role |
+|------|------|
+| **Python** | The glue language |
+| **Hugging Face Transformers** | Fast, free, offline-capable sentiment model |
+| **OpenAI API** | Deep reasoning + aspect analysis |
+| **Gradio** | Instant web UI without any HTML/CSS |
+| **LLMOps practices** | Prompt versioning + response logging |
+
+---
+
+## 🗓️ The 6-Day Plan
+
+Each day builds **directly on the previous day**. Don't skip ahead — the magic is in the progression.
+
+| Day | Theme | What you'll build |
+|-----|-------|-------------------|
+| [Day 1](./Day-1) | **Foundations & First Sentiment Script** | Setup Python env, install Hugging Face, run your first sentiment prediction in 10 lines |
+| [Day 2](./Day-2) | **Adding OpenAI for Deep Reasoning** | Plug in OpenAI API, learn prompt engineering, get sentiment + reasoning |
+| [Day 3](./Day-3) | **Building the Gradio Interface** | Turn your Day 2 script into a real web app anyone can use |
+| [Day 4](./Day-4) | **Batch Reviews & Side-by-Side Comparison** | Analyse many reviews at once, compare HF vs OpenAI in a table with confidence bars |
+| [Day 5](./Day-5) | **Aspect Analysis + Overall Score + Keywords** | Extract *what* customers love/hate, compute a product score, language detection |
+| [Day 6](./Day-6) | **LLMOps Polish + Final App** | Prompt versioning, CSV logging, deployment notes — and your finished portfolio project |
+
+---
+
+## ✅ Before You Start (Prerequisites)
+
+- Basic Python (variables, functions, lists, dicts)
+- Python 3.9 or newer installed
+- An **OpenAI API key** (you'll only need it from Day 2 onwards)
+- Curiosity 🙂
+
+You do **not** need to know:
+- Machine learning theory
+- Web development (Gradio handles it)
+- Deployment (we cover it on Day 6)
+
+---
+
+## 📐 How Each Day Is Structured
+
+Every day's README follows the same pattern so your brain knows what to expect:
+
+1. **🎯 What you'll learn today** — bullet points
+2. **🤔 The problem** — the real pain point we're solving
+3. **💡 The solution** — the high-level idea, in plain English
+4. **🧑‍💻 The code** — short, readable, and **explained line-by-line**
+5. **▶️ Try it yourself** — exact commands to run
+6. **🔭 Tomorrow's preview** — what we'll add next
+
+The code is intentionally **short and simple**. We always pick the *clearest* line over the *cleverest* line.
+
